  "text": "In the paper [CITATION_1] , Kuijlaars found explicit formulas for the entries of the solution to the tacnode RHP in terms of Airy functions and related operators. He found six solutions to the differ-ential equation (1.18a) with q(σ) being the Hastings-McLeod solution to PII, which were labeled m (0) , . . . , m [CITATION_2] . Let us remark here that in the case (t 1 , t 2 , t 3 ) = (1, 0, −1), the solutions n (0) , . . . , n [CITATION_3] constructed in this paper agree with the ones constructed by Kuijlaars up to sign. Specifically we have ",
